    <p class="text-sm text-[var(--fg-secondary)] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-pretty">
      HomePlanningHub helps homeowners, DIY renovators, and contractors perform accurate construction material takeoffs for common home renovation planning and DIY construction estimation. Whether you are estimating concrete yardage for a patio, calculating how many shingle bundles your roof needs, figuring out how many gallons of paint cover a bedroom, or working out tile counts for a bathroom floor — each calculator converts your room dimensions into precise material quantities using standard engineering formulas and manufacturer-published coverage rates.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm text-[var(--fg-secondary)] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-pretty">
      The goal is to give you a reliable material estimate before you visit the hardware store or call a contractor. Running short mid-project means costly reload fees and schedule delays. Over-ordering means wasted money and materials that sit unused in your garage. A careful quantity takeoff — matched to your actual project dimensions — helps you avoid both outcomes and keeps your home improvement budgeting on track.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm text-[var(--fg-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-pretty">
      Beyond simple quantities, a good estimate helps you compare material options. Should you pour a concrete driveway or lay asphalt? Will architectural shingles cost less than a standing-seam metal roof over the full lifespan of your home? Our material comparison pages show these tradeoffs with the same project dimensions, so the decision is grounded in hard numbers rather than guesswork.
    </p>
